gomodel:SYNGO_2789  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Background: IntDen=the product of an area and the average gray value within that area\n\n[Fig.2: \"The density and IntDen of GFP-actin and Syn-RFP clusters are increased following ALLN treatment\"\n- \"Together, these results demonstrate that ALLN treatment enhances the accumulation of actin at discrete sites along the axon and mediates the recruitment of SVs to these sites.\"]\n\nFig.5: \"The IntDen of synaptic GFP-actin clusters is decreased in neurons with reduced β-pix activity.\"\n\nFig.6: \"The localization of synaptic vesicles at synapses is disrupted in neurons with reduced β-pix activity\". Experimental description: - \"To suppress expression of endogenous β-pix, three interfering RNA oligonucleotides against rat β-pix (Invitrogen) were transiently transfected into rat hippocampal neurons. \" Species of neurons is therefore rat." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2018-03-07" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_2789" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

